// CATEGORY: Contouring/Firming Products
promptContourBodyStructure claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Body Structure/Function Alteration (Contouring Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 4 (Contouring/Firming), p.25\n\n",
    "Principle: Contouring cosmetics can only claim to improve the APPEARANCE of skin,\n",
    "helping it look naturally firm according to individual structure. They cannot\n",
    "claim to alter body functions or structure.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (appearance improvement):\n",
    "  - \"improves the appearance of the skin\"\n",
    "  - \"helps facial or body skin look naturally firm\"\n",
    "  - \"according to each individual's natural structure\"\n",
    "  - \"appearance of firmness\"\n",
    "  - Temporary cosmetic effect on how skin looks\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (structural/functional alteration):\n",
    "  - \"increases metabolism\"\n",
    "  - \"reduces fat accumulation\" / \"breaks down fat\"\n",
    "  - \"improves blood circulation\"\n",
    "  - \"reduces waist size\"\n",
    "  - \"increases or decreases breast size\"\n",
    "  - \"reduces cellulite\"\n",
    "  - \"firms body contours\" (if implying structural change)\n",
    "  - \"reshapes the face\" (if implying structural change)\n",
    "  - Any claim about altering body functions or structure\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Appearance of firmness ✓ vs. actual structural/functional alteration ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this claim imply efficacy in ALTERING BODY FUNCTIONS OR STRUCTURE\n",
    "(metabolism, fat, circulation, size, cellulite), rather than just improving appearance?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates contouring rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Exfoliating Products
promptExfoliateStructural claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Skin Structural Alteration (Exfoliating Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 5 (Exfoliating), p.26\n\n",
    "Principle: Exfoliating cosmetics can only claim to improve skin appearance by\n",
    "removing dead skin cells (chemical/physical exfoliation). They cannot claim to\n",
    "alter skin structure, stimulate formation, or affect underlying conditions.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (surface appearance improvement):\n",
    "  - \"exfoliates\" / \"removes dead skin cells\"\n",
    "  - \"smooth skin\"\n",
    "  - \"radiant skin\"\n",
    "  - \"improves skin appearance\"\n",
    "  - Products with AHA, scrub beads, etc. for cell turnover\n",
    "  - Surface-level cosmetic effects\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (structural alteration):\n",
    "  - \"peels skin to make it bright\" (implies structural change)\n",
    "  - \"stimulates or enhances new skin formation\"\n",
    "  - \"stimulates collagen formation\"\n",
    "  - \"reduces acne, melasma, freckles\" (therapeutic)\n",
    "  - \"makes skin much whiter than before\" (structural pigmentation change)\n",
    "  - \"just scrubbing makes skin white\"\n",
    "  - \"scrub breaks down subcutaneous fat\"\n",
    "  - \"scrub tightens pores\" (structural change)\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Removing dead surface cells ✓ vs. stimulating new formation or altering structure ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this claim imply efficacy in ALTERING SKIN STRUCTURE, stimulating\n",
    "formation (skin/collagen), or affecting underlying conditions, rather than just\n",
    "removing dead surface cells?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates exfoliating rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Cleansing Products - Medical Symbols
promptCleansingMedicalSymbols claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Medical Symbols/Imagery (Cleansing Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 7 (Cleansing), p.29\n\n",
    "Principle: Cleansing cosmetics cannot use images, symbols, or marks that could\n",
    "mislead consumers into thinking the product is medicinal. This includes medical\n",
    "symbols, cross marks, germ-killing imagery, and specific prohibited symbols.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (cosmetic imagery):\n",
    "  - Standard product imagery\n",
    "  - Cleansing/hygiene imagery\n",
    "  - Trademarks with clear ® or TM designation\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (medical/misleading symbols):\n",
    "  - Cross mark\n",
    "  - Rx symbol\n",
    "  - Red Cross symbol (specifically prohibited)\n",
    "  - Shield symbol\n",
    "  - Overlay lines suggesting germ killing\n",
    "  - Images of microbial structures\n",
    "  - Images suggesting a specific germ\n",
    "  - Any symbol/mark that could mislead consumers about medicinal properties\n",
    "  - Trademarks without clear ® or TM (if could be mistaken for medical)\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Standard cosmetic imagery ✓ vs. medical/germ-killing symbols ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this advertising: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this advertising USE IMAGES, SYMBOLS, OR MARKS that could mislead\n",
    "consumers into thinking the product is medicinal (crosses, Rx, Red Cross, shields,\n",
    "germ-killing imagery, microbial structures)?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates cleansing symbol rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Anti-Dandruff Products
promptDandruffTherapeutic claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Dandruff Therapeutic Claims (Anti-Dandruff Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 8 (Anti-Dandruff), p.30\n\n",
    "Principle: Anti-dandruff cosmetics can only claim cosmetic cleansing of hair,\n",
    "scalp, and dandruff flakes, plus reducing itchiness caused by dandruff during\n",
    "use. They cannot claim therapeutic effects like eliminating fungal itch, treating\n",
    "inflammation, or permanently removing dandruff.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (cosmetic cleansing during use):\n",
    "  - \"cleansing hair, scalp, and dandruff flakes\"\n",
    "  - \"reducing scalp itchiness caused by dandruff\"\n",
    "  - \"during the period of product use\"\n",
    "  - Cosmetic scope effects only\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (therapeutic claims):\n",
    "  - \"eliminating or inhibiting scalp itch caused by fungi\"\n",
    "  - \"treating scalp inflammation\"\n",
    "  - \"permanently removing dandruff\"\n",
    "  - \"cures dandruff\"\n",
    "  - \"eliminates dandruff\" (implies permanence)\n",
    "  - Any therapeutic or permanent effect\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Cosmetic cleansing during use ✓ vs. therapeutic treatment or permanent elimination ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this claim imply therapeutic efficacy (ELIMINATING FUNGAL ITCH,\n",
    "TREATING INFLAMMATION, PERMANENTLY REMOVING DANDRUFF) rather than cosmetic\n",
    "cleansing during use?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates anti-dandruff rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Hair Care Products - Unspecified Hair Loss
promptHaircareUnspecifiedLoss claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Unspecified Hair Loss Claims (Hair Care Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 9 (Hair Care), p.31\n\n",
    "Principle: Hair care cosmetics can only claim to reduce hair loss from specific\n",
    "cosmetic causes (tangled, brittle, dry, damaged hair). They cannot claim to\n",
    "reduce hair loss without specifying the cause, or claim to reduce loss from\n",
    "internal factors (hair cycle, scalp conditions, genetics).\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (specified cosmetic causes):\n",
    "  - \"reduces breakage / hair loss from brittle, dry, damaged, or tangled hair\"\n",
    "  - \"makes hair smooth and easy to comb, reduces breakage and hair loss caused\n",
    "    by tangled hair\"\n",
    "  - \"nourishes hair / helps hair stay strong from root to tip\" (cosmetic meaning)\n",
    "  - Must specify the cosmetic cause\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (unspecified or internal causes):\n",
    "  - \"reduces hair loss\" (without specifying cause)\n",
    "  - \"prevents hair loss\"\n",
    "  - Implies reducing loss from internal factors\n",
    "  - Implies reducing loss from hair growth cycle issues\n",
    "  - Implies reducing loss from scalp conditions\n",
    "  - Implies reducing loss from genetic traits\n",
    "  - \"reduces hair fall / hair loss due to hair shedding from hair roots located\n",
    "    in the dermis\"\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Specified cosmetic cause (tangled/brittle/dry/damaged) ✓ vs.\n",
    "unspecified or internal causes ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this claim assert hair loss reduction WITHOUT SPECIFYING the\n",
    "cosmetic cause, or imply reducing loss from internal/medical factors?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates hair care rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Hair Care Products - Deep Nourishment
