// CATEGORY: Oral Care - Toothpaste - Disease Claims
promptToothpasteDiseaseClms claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Disease Treatment/Prevention (Toothpaste Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 14.1 (Toothpaste), p.35-39\n\n",
    "Principle: Toothpaste can claim cleaning, promoting oral/dental hygiene, and\n",
    "preventing dental caries IF containing tested preventive ingredients like fluoride.\n",
    "Cannot claim treating or preventing dental diseases (ulcers, fungal infections,\n",
    "gingivitis, bleeding gums).\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (hygiene and prevention with proper ingredients):\n",
    "  - \"cleaning and promoting oral/dental hygiene\"\n",
    "  - \"preventing dental caries\" (if contains fluoride or tested ingredients)\n",
    "  - \"reducing accumulation of bacterial plaque\" (from proper brushing)\n",
    "  - \"reducing tooth sensitivity\" (if contains desensitizing agents)\n",
    "  - \"makes teeth white\" (from polishing/cleaning effect)\n",
    "  - Proper substantiation required\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (disease treatment/prevention):\n",
    "  - \"treating or preventing dental diseases\"\n",
    "  - \"mouth ulcers\"\n",
    "  - \"oral fungal infections\"\n",
    "  - \"gingivitis\"\n",
    "  - \"bleeding gums\"\n",
    "  - Any disease treatment or prevention claims\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Hygiene + tested caries prevention ✓ vs. disease treatment ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this toothpaste claim imply TREATING or PREVENTING DENTAL DISEASES\n",
    "(ulcers, fungal infections, gingivitis, bleeding gums)?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates toothpaste rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
