promptTeethwhitenEnamelAbnormal claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Enamel Abnormality Whitening (Teeth Whitening Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 15 (Teeth Whitening), p.39\n\n",
    "Principle: Teeth whitening cosmetics cannot claim to whiten teeth affected by\n",
    "enamel abnormalities, tetracycline use, or fluorosis, as these conditions cannot\n",
    "be corrected by cosmetic whitening. Must include disclaimers about variable\n",
    "results and recommend dentist supervision.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (realistic whitening with disclaimers):\n",
    "  - Whitening claims for normal teeth\n",
    "  - Must reflect reality or include: \"results may vary depending on natural\n",
    "    color of each person's teeth\"\n",
    "  - Recommended: \"use under supervision of a dentist\"\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (unrealistic whitening claims):\n",
    "  - \"whitens teeth affected by enamel abnormalities\"\n",
    "  - \"whitens teeth affected by tetracycline use\"\n",
    "  - \"whitens teeth affected by excessive fluoride intake in childhood\" (fluorosis)\n",
    "  - Any claim about whitening teeth with structural abnormalities\n\n",
    "Note: Oral hygiene products with ≤0.1% hydrogen peroxide may be sold but must\n",
    "not claim whitening efficacy.\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Normal teeth whitening ✓ vs. enamel abnormality whitening ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this teeth whitening claim imply whitening teeth AFFECTED BY\n",
    "ENAMEL ABNORMALITIES, TETRACYCLINE, or FLUOROSIS?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
