    "factual information, provided they don't mislead about the product being cosmetic\n",
    "(not medicinal). Plus signs, crosses, or similar symbols must clearly indicate\n",
    "meaning and not exceed cosmetic scope. Cannot use symbols suggesting medical\n",
    "treatment.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (non-medical certifications):\n",
    "  - GMP/ISO/Halal logos with proper documentation\n",
    "  - Plus signs indicating added ingredients (\"VITAMIN B... Hyaluronic\")\n",
    "  - Meaning clearly indicated\n",
    "  - Does not mislead about cosmetic nature\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (medical symbols):\n",
    "  - Symbols suggesting treatment/alleviation/cure/prevention/pathogen killing\n",
    "  - Red cross on white background (Red Cross Act BE 2499)\n",
    "  - White cross on red/green background\n",
    "  - White on green background\n",
    "  - Plus signs resembling medical facility symbols\n",
    "  - Plus/cross with medical symbols/wording/images (Rod of Asclepius,\n",
    "    \"Hospital,\" \"Clinic\") unless clearly part of registered trademark with ®\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Non-medical certification marks ✓ vs. medical symbols ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this advertising: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this advertising USE SYMBOLS, LOGOS, OR MARKS suggesting MEDICAL\n",
    "TREATMENT (crosses, medical facility symbols, Rod of Asclepius) or the Red Cross\n",
    "symbol?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates certified product symbol rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Certified Products - Unregistered Medical Terms
promptCertifiedMedicalTerms claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Unregistered Medical Terms (Certified Products Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 21 (Certified Products), p.43\n\n",
    "Principle: Cannot use plus signs or cross symbols combined with medical symbols/\n",
    "wording/images implying diagnosis, treatment, alleviation, cure, or prevention\n",
    "of diseases, UNLESS clearly part of a registered trademark with ®.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE:\n",
    "  - Medical-related symbols clearly part of registered trademark with ®\n",
    "  - Non-medical certification marks\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (unregistered medical terminology):\n",
    "  - Plus/cross with: \"diagnosis,\" \"treatment,\" \"alleviation,\" \"cure,\"\n",
    "    \"prevention\" of diseases\n",
    "  - Rod of Asclepius (medical symbol)\n",
    "  - Words: \"Hospital,\" \"Clinic\"\n",
    "  - Unless clearly part of registered trademark with ®\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Registered trademark with ® ✓ vs. unregistered medical terms ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this advertising: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this advertising USE MEDICAL TERMINOLOGY or SYMBOLS (diagnosis/\n",
    "treatment/cure/prevention, Rod of Asclepius, Hospital/Clinic) WITHOUT a clearly\n",
    "visible registered trademark ®?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates certified product rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Comparison/Sales Claims
promptComparisonCompetitor claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Competitor Comparison (Comparison Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 22 (Comparison Products), p.44\n\n",
    "Principle: Cosmetics may compare own product's sales over time or display sales\n",
    "ranking within same product group in specific area/period with documentation.\n",
    "Cannot compare with different products, different companies, or mention other\n",
    "product names.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (own-product comparison):\n",
    "  - Compare own product's sales over surveyed period\n",
    "  - Present production records/supporting evidence\n",
    "  - Compare sales of same product group in specific area with:\n",
    "    * Time period specified\n",
    "    * Area specified (e.g., Bangkok, specific store)\n",
    "    * Factual supporting documents\n",
    "    * Sales ranking within same product group\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (competitor comparison):\n",
    "  - Compare with different products\n",
    "  - Compare with different companies\n",
    "  - Mention other product names\n",
    "  - \"Better than [Brand X]\"\n",
    "  - \"Outsells [competitor]\"\n",
    "  - \"#1 vs. [other brand]\"\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Own-product sales comparison ✓ vs. competitor comparison ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this comparison claim COMPARE WITH DIFFERENT PRODUCTS, DIFFERENT\n",
    "COMPANIES, or MENTION OTHER PRODUCT NAMES?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates comparison rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

// CATEGORY: Statistical Claims
promptStatisticalSatisfactionEfficacy claimText MEANS
  CONCAT
    "REGULATORY TEST: Satisfaction vs. Efficacy (Statistical Claims Category)\n",
    "Context: Thai Cosmetics Manual BE 2567, Category 23 (Statistical Claims), p.45\n\n",
    "Principle: Cosmetics may reference customer satisfaction test results with proper\n",
    "disclosure (sample size, percentage, time, tested group). Cannot claim the\n",
    "product is EFFECTIVE based solely on satisfaction tests, as satisfaction tests\n",
    "are not scientific efficacy tests. Clinical efficacy testing requires\n",
    "internationally recognized methods and proper scientific documentation.\n\n",
    "Decision Boundary:\n",
    "✅ ACCEPTABLE (satisfaction testing with disclosure):\n",
    "  - Satisfaction test results cited directly (\"45 out of 50 people\") or as\n",
    "    percentage with total sample size\n",
    "  - Tested sample group indicated (\"women,\" \"consumers,\" \"users,\" \"volunteer\n",
    "    group\")\n",
    "  - Includes text: \"customer satisfaction test\"\n",
    "  - For TV/radio: statement clearly spoken with/without superimposed text\n",
    "  - Proper disclosure of methodology\n\n",
    "❌ PROHIBITED (efficacy claims from satisfaction tests):\n",
    "  - Claiming product is \"EFFECTIVE\" based solely on satisfaction test results\n",
    "  - Treating satisfaction tests as scientific efficacy tests\n",
    "  - Missing required disclosures (sample size, methodology)\n\n",
    "For clinical efficacy testing:\n",
    "  - Must be based on test results of advertised product\n",
    "  - Must follow internationally recognized methods\n",
    "  - Must specify: what was tested, testing period, testing conditions,\n",
    "    statistical methods, number of volunteers\n\n",
    "Key distinction: Satisfaction testing with disclosure ✓ vs. efficacy claims from satisfaction tests ✗\n\n",
    "Evaluate this claim: ", claimText, "\n\n",
    "Question: Does this statistical claim assert the product is EFFECTIVE based\n",
    "solely on SATISFACTION TEST RESULTS, rather than clinical efficacy testing?\n\n",
    "Answer with:\n",
    "- YES (violates statistical rules - prohibited) or NO (acceptable)\n",
    "- Confidence: [0-100]%\n",
    "- Reasoning: [1-2 sentences explaining your judgment]"

